author: JOE KENT
title: Cooler temps bring out flounder, croaker
text:
Daily News has an ax to grind 
Editor’s note: Read the Daily News’ rebuttal in the Sunday paper. 
I f you have the impression that The Galveston County Daily News has an ax to grind against the Galveston County Commissioners Court, you’re not alone. A ship’s door to a sunrise 
S ound asleep from the gentle rocking of the ship’s bow, a laser light hits my eyes. Mother is up to use the restroom. After she climbs back in her couch convert bed, I peek out the curtain. Lights twinkle in the distance. Cargo shorts go on and in three steps I am out on the 11th foredeck of the Magic.
